[SN]TITLE[SN]
Man arrested after Derby hit-and-run death

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A man has been arrested in connection with the hit-and-run death of another man in Derby.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Satnam Singh, 74, was found with serious injuries on Coronation Street in the early hours of 23 July.
Mr Singh, a Sikh volunteer who was a community leader, died later in hospital.
The man, 34, from Derby, was arrested on suspicion of causing death by dangerous driving and was released on police bail.
He was found injured on Friday morning near the Sikh temple where he worked as a volunteer.
Detectives are trying to trace a dark hatchback car seen in the area.
A post-mortem examination revealed he died from head and chest injuries "consistent with being hit by a vehicle", Derbyshire Police said.
